<section id="portfolio">
  <div class="inner reveal">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow"><div class="sec-line"></div><span>Portfolio</span></div>
    <h2>Writing Samples</h2>
    <div class="port-tabs">
      <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="switchTab('articles',this)">Articles & Blog Posts</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('products',this)">Product Descriptions</button>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-content active" id="tab-articles">
      <div class="port-item">
        <div class="port-header" onclick="togglePort(this)">
          <div>
            <div class="port-meta"><span class="port-type">Article</span><span class="port-niche">Health & Psychology</span></div>
            <div class="port-title">Social Media Is Quietly Damaging Your Mental Health</div>
            <div class="port-excerpt">A research-backed deep dive into how platforms rewire your brain — and what you can do about it.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="port-arrow">▼</div>
        </div>
        <div class="port-body">
          <div class="port-content">
            <h3>Social Media Is Quietly Damaging Your Mental Health</h3>
            <div class="pmeta">Article &nbsp;·&nbsp; Health & Psychology &nbsp;·&nbsp; ~1,200 words &nbsp;·&nbsp; Informative & Empathetic</div>
            <p>Most people think of social media as a neutral tool — something you pick up, use, and put down. But that is not quite how it works inside your brain.</p>
            <p>Every like, comment, and notification triggers a small release of dopamine — the chemical your brain associates with reward and pleasure. Over time, your brain starts craving that hit. You check your phone more often. You feel restless without it. <strong>10% of social media users in the U.S. show signs of problematic use</strong> — and most do not recognise the pattern until it is already affecting their daily life.</p>
            <h4>Social Media Anxiety: Why You Feel Tense Even When Nothing Is Wrong</h4>
            <p>Psychologists describe it as "ambient anxiety" — a low-level tension that lingers because you are always half-connected. <strong>41% of Gen Z users say social media makes them feel sad or anxious.</strong> But adults are far from immune — the pressure to respond quickly and maintain an online presence creates a performance loop with no clear off switch.</p>
            <h4>The Link Between Heavy Use and Depression</h4>
            <p>Research links heavy social media use to a 70% increase in self-reported depression symptoms among teenagers. Around 78% of people use social media right before bed, directly disrupting sleep quality and worsening mood and concentration the following day.</p>
            <h4>How to Protect Your Mental Health</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Set a daily limit of 30–60 minutes using your phone's built-in screen time tracker</li>
              <li>Unfollow accounts that consistently make you feel worse about yourself</li>
              <li>No phone for the last hour before bed — sleep quality has a direct line to mental health</li>
              <li>Replace passive scrolling with active connection — call or text someone directly</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Digital well-being is not about perfection. It is about making small, deliberate choices that add up over time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="port-item">
        <div class="port-header" onclick="togglePort(this)">
          <div>
            <div class="port-meta"><span class="port-type">Article</span><span class="port-niche">Business & Marketing</span></div>
            <div class="port-title">Content Marketing for Small Businesses: Your Roadmap to Growth in 2026</div>
            <div class="port-excerpt">Why content marketing is the smartest investment a small business can make — and a clear framework to get started.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="port-arrow">▼</div>
        </div>
        <div class="port-body">
          <div class="port-content">
            <h3>Content Marketing for Small Businesses: Your Roadmap to Growth in 2026</h3>
            <div class="pmeta">Article &nbsp;·&nbsp; Business & Marketing &nbsp;·&nbsp; ~1,400 words &nbsp;·&nbsp; Educational & Authoritative</div>
            <p>Did you know that content marketing generates 3x more leads than outbound marketing — at a fraction of the cost? If you are running a
